Package net.objectzoo.delegates

This package contains the delegates of the Events4J API.
  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Action<T>
    An Action is a reference to a procedure without return value that can be invoked synchronously similar to a regular Java method call.
    Action0
    An Action0 is a reference to a procedure without return value that can be invoked synchronously similar to a regular Java method call.
    Action0Async
    An Action0Async is a reference to a procedure without return value that can be invoked asynchronously in another thread.
    Action2<T1,​T2>
    An Action2 is a reference to a procedure without return value that can be invoked synchronously similar to a regular Java method call.
    Action2Async<T1,​T2>
    An Action2Async is a reference to a procedure without return value that can be invoked asynchronously in another thread.
    Action3<T1,​T2,​T3>
    An Action3 is a reference to a procedure without return value that can be invoked synchronously similar to a regular Java method call.
    Action3Async<T1,​T2,​T3>
    An Action3Async is a reference to a procedure without return value that can be invoked asynchronously in another thread.
    Action4<T1,​T2,​T3,​T4>
    An Action4 is a reference to a procedure without return value that can be invoked synchronously similar to a regular Java method call.
    Action4Async<T1,​T2,​T3,​T4>
    An Action4Async is a reference to a procedure without return value that can be invoked asynchronously in another thread.
    ActionAsync<T>
    An ActionAsync is a reference to a procedure without return value that can be invoked asynchronously in another thread.
    ActionAsyncResult
    A ActionAsyncResult represents the result of an ActionAsync invocation.

    Function3<T1,​T2,​T3,​R>

    Function3Async<T1,​T2,​T3,​R>
    A Function3Async is a reference to a function with return value that can be invoked asynchronously in another thread.
    Function4<T1,​T2,​T3,​T4,​R>
